stat:
returns a stat structure with information about a file.

rename:
renames a file, any hard links to the file are unaffected.

returns 0 on success, -1 on error.

truncate:
truncates a file to be of precisely a set length of bytes. 
Any extra bytes are lost and "missing" bytes reads as null bytes ('\0').

returns 0 on success, -1 on error.

unlink:
delete a name from the filesystem. If that name was the last link to a file
the file is deleted.

returns 0 on success, -1 on error

lseek


--/usr/include/fuse/fuse.h--
